beer.beer_description:
Mirror Mirror on the wall, who’s the oatiest of them all? Introducing our 100% Oat IPA. Using just oats and a little lactose for body, we also added oat milk to double down on oaty goodness.

Coming in at 6.5% ABV, this creamy IPA pours a hazy pale colour, with a generous double dry hop of Riwaka, Idaho and Amarillo to round things off.

items.checkin_comment: Oats on oats on oats. Was expecting a super smooth creamy beer, but was greeted by a meaty fairly bitter and heavily hopped brew. Not much in the way of oaty sweetness. Bit of off-putting astringent hop burn on the back.

Keeping my friends close,
 but my beers closer.
Beer, whiskey and coffee are my loves! I use the uni scoring system for my ratings, and love both strong and light beers
Yorkshireman, CAMRA Member and beer drinker!
Just a ordinary guy in search for extraordinary beers
Step aside coffee. This is a job for beer.
I just enjoy drinking in foreign theme parks
